    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the write-back tool in `WorkingDocumentTools.cs` that updates `sprk_analysisoutput.sprk_workingdocument` with the AI-generated content. This tool must ONLY execute after plan approval (called from the plan execution in task 072) and must NEVER modify the SPE source file. Verify the existing `WorkingDocumentTools.cs` and extend or replace as needed.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in Dataverse SDK and the BFF AI tool pipeline. CRITICAL: Never write to SPE files from this tool.
  </role>

  <goal>
    WriteBackToAnalysisOutput tool exists in the BFF; when called post-approval, it updates `sprk_analysisoutput.sprk_workingdocument` field in Dataverse with the provided content; returns success/failure with the updated content.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The write-back targets `sprk_analysisoutput.sprk_workingdocument` — a Dataverse field (likely a multi-line text or HTML field) on the analysis output record. The SPE source file (stored in SharePoint Embedded) must NEVER be modified. The existing `WorkingDocumentTools.cs` may already have a partial implementation — read it first. The tool is invoked as part of an approved plan execution (from task 072), not directly from the agent loop.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatDataverseRepository.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec-FR-12">MUST NOT modify SPE source files — write ONLY to sprk_analysisoutput.sprk_workingdocument</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST be plan-preview-gated (only called from approved plan execution)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Access Dataverse via existing repository pattern — no raw SDK calls</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-workspace-companion/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="WorkingDocumentTools existing" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs">
        Read this file FIRST — there may already be a write-back tool. Extend or complete it rather than creating from scratch.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Dataverse repository" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatDataverseRepository.cs">
        Follow existing Dataverse update patterns.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read WorkingDocumentTools.cs and ChatDataverseRepository.cs in full</step>
    <step order="2">Identify if WriteBackToWorkingDocument (or similar) already exists; if so, verify it targets sprk_analysisoutput and extend</step>
    <step order="3">Implement or verify UpdateWorkingDocument method in ChatDataverseRepository.cs: update sprk_workingdocument field on the analysis output record</step>
    <step order="4">In WriteBackToWorkingDocument tool: call the repository method with analysisOutputId and content</step>
    <step order="5">Add validation: MUST NOT call any SPE/Graph SDK file write methods from this tool</step>
    <step order="6">Add the write-back tool to the compound intent detection list (task 071) so it always triggers plan preview gate</step>
    <step order="7">Build BFF: dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/</step>
    <step order="8">Run existing BFF tests to verify no regressions: dotnet test tests/</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 073 status to ✅ completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test .NET project</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given WriteBackToWorkingDocument tool, when called with analysisOutputId and content, then sprk_workingdocument field is updated in Dataverse.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given WriteBackToWorkingDocument tool, when inspected, then no SPE/Graph file write SDK calls are present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF builds without errors; existing tests pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The sprk_workingdocument field type needs to be verified (likely nvarchar(max) or HTML/memo). Update accordingly. The Dataverse update call: use existing Dataverse SDK patterns in ChatDataverseRepository.cs. The analysisOutputId is available from the SprkChat session context (added when the analysis workspace launched SprkChat with analysisId). Double-check: the update targets sprk_analysisoutput entity, NOT the SharePoint document. This is the most critical safety constraint in the entire project.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
